HEADWORD: Decoy-duck
<hw>De*coy"-duck`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A duck used to
lure wild ducks into a decoy; hence, a person employed to lure others
into danger.</def> <rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

